Use file chooser to set TaskPaper document to work on (d:choosedoc)

# A normal file filter seems never show results until you start typing. Here is a hand rolled one.
from subprocess import check_output import os import sys import json
jxascript_alert=""" app = Application.currentApplication() app.includeStandardAdditions = true app.displayAlert('Spotlight could not find any TaskPaper documents.',{message: 'Select document with command: d:choosedoc'}) """
# This gets a privalage violation from JXA so this script is in python find_cmd = "mdfind \"kMDItemContentType == 'com.taskpaper.text'\"" find_cmd_result = check_output(find_cmd, shell=True)
if not find_cmd_result: # No documents found dialogue_cmd = 'osascript -l JavaScript -e "%s"' % jxascript_alert check_output(dialogue_cmd, shell=True) path_list = [] else: path_list = find_cmd_result.split('\n')
items = [] for path in path_list: if '/Library/Application Support/TaskPaper/Configurations/' in path: continue
items.append({ 'uid': path, 'title': os.path.basename(path).split('.')[0], 'subtitle': path, 'arg': path, 'icon': { 'path': 'icon.png' } })
sys.stdout.write(json.dumps({'items': items}))
